- Move `Dual` and `dualPairing` lower in the import-hierachy
- deduplicate `dualPairing`
- Bundle continuity statements to `CLM`s.
- Make `WeakDual` and `WeakSpace` reducible
- Remove `refine'` in favor of `refine`

---

While you're touching this line, would you like to replace `refine'` by `refine`?
There [seems to be](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/refine.20vs.20refine') consensus for this in principle (there are just too many occurrences to rewrite them all by hand).

```suggestion
```

Is there a consensus that `Dual` with this meaning can be in the root namespace? Currently it is in `NormedSpace.Dual`. It seems quite clear indeed that `NormedSpace` namespace is not the best choice anymore (not general enough), but in my opinion this PR's proposal to change directly to the root namespace requires a wide agreement, because dual might be standard terminology in other contexts as well. In fact I might personally favor putting the algebraic dual of a vector space in the root namespace as `Dual`. For the topological dual, there should be some indication of topology in the fully qualified name.
I think the topological dual is more meaningful than the algebraic one. However, it would be the least confusing if both are not in the root namespace and have an indication which one they are.

This indeed looks like a more appropriate place for the file where the dual space is defined.

I think the module docstring of this new file should briefly explain the meaning of the concept of dual (however standard) as well as the notation `->L[k]` (which is not standard in mathematics, only standard in parts of Mathlib). The docstring of the file [`NormedSpace.Dual`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/f2eace05e038fd0f6da83e3604db037040d89d54/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Dual.lean) contained an appropriate amount of detail in my opinion. Copying the authorship from there would also seem appropriate at least unless the contents substantially change or are expanded.
I wrote a bit in the module docstring. I added you to the list of authors as well since I took the content from the `WeakDual`-file

I really don't love this renaming. It's not the dual of a topological space, it's the dual of a topological *vector* space. How about `ContinuousLinearMap.Dual`? It's not perfect either, but I think it captures things better. And probably you'll want that namespace open when working with this anyway.

Same comments apply to the other definitions moved into this namespace.
And what about `Topology.Dual`? If you don't like it I'm fine with `ContinuousLinearMap` as well, and we can always change it later.

```suggestion
```

This sentence in the module docstring seems to have become weird, due to the addition of Banach-Alaoglu. I suggest simply removing it.
Aren't we supposed to put the imports in alphabetical order? I can never remember.
Did you mean to delete this comment ? It seems still relevant, although maybe a bit useless.
I think this is still relevant ? As in, one could want to use `deriving` ?
